<section class="section has-background-light">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="columns is-multiline">
      <div class="column is-10-mobile is-10-tablet is-6-desktop">
        <img src="/assets/images/data-sources.png" class="img--rounded img--bordered" alt="Screenshot of the website that the Flemish Government uses to display their application profiles and data models.">
      </div>
      <div class="column is-5 is-offset-1-desktop is-7-tablet is-5-desktop">
        <h2 class="title is-4">Fueled by their own data model<br>&amp; multiple data sources</h2>
        <div class="content">
          <p>
            Local governments make decisions while using <a href="https://data.vlaanderen.be/ns#Applicatieprofielen" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">application profiles [dutch]</a> and data sources such as:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>their representatives, members of the administrative body. View the <a href="https://data.vlaanderen.be/ns/mandaat" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">data model for mandate [dutch]</a>;</li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://data.vlaanderen.be/ns/besluit" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">local decisions [dutch]</a> made by local governments;
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://data.vlaanderen.be/doc/applicatieprofiel/verkeersborden/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">road signs [dutch]</a> and <a href="https://data.vlaanderen.be/doc/applicatieprofiel/besluit-mobiliteit/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">mobility [dutch]</a>;
            </li>
            <li>
              legislation from the <a href="https://codex.vlaanderen.be/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Flemish codex [dutch]</a>,
              <a href="https://data.vlaanderen.be/doc/applicatieprofiel/vlaamse-codex/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">accompanied with a data model [dutch]</a>.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The application keeps evolving, and adds more data sources and -models along the way. Because of the <LinkTo @route="docs">plugin system</LinkTo> it is easy to extend the application with more functionality.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="columns is-multiline">
      <div class="column is-8-tablet is-5-desktop">
        <h2 class="title is-4">Used by local governments before, during and after their council meetings</h2>
        <div class="content">
          <p>
            Local governments hold council meetings every month. Their meeting minutes contain valuable information for multiple organisations and individuals &mdash; which is why Say helps to <strong>structure documents semantically</strong> in a
            way that makes <strong>data-sharing and -reuse</strong> possible.
          </p>
          <p>
            Say recognises what is typed, and <strong>enriches the decisions made during the council meetings with links to other relevant resources and metadata</strong>.
            By <strong>signing, publishing and distributing these smart documents in a standardised and linked way</strong>, no information gathered in those council meetings gets lost.
          </p>
          <p>
            The editor allows local governments to sign, publish and distribute their documents with ease. On top of that, they can <strong>connect with other (custom) services they are currently using</strong>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="column is-10-mobile is-10-tablet is-6-desktop is-offset-1-desktop">
        <img src="/assets/images/say-partner-LBLOD-editor.jpg" alt="Picture of a laptop with the editor branded for the Flemish Government.">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="columns is-multiline">
      <div class="column is-10-mobile is-10-tablet is-5-desktop">
        <img src="/assets/images/say-partner-LBLOD-reuse.jpg" alt="Screenshots of government applications that reuse data that has been created by the editor.">
      </div>
      <div class="column is-8-tablet is-5-desktop is-offset-1-desktop">
        <div class="content">
          <h2 class="title is-4">Reused by multiple<br>organisations &amp; individuals</h2>
          <p>
            The information that local governments have shared in their documents, can be reused by different people on different platforms:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Local governments themselves</strong>
              <br>For example: local governments will not have to keep a track record of mandates manually; if it's written in a Say document, they can automatically feed other applications with this information.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>The Flemish Government</strong>
              <br>decisions that need to be reported at the Flemish Government flow through automatically. Nobody needs to send or notify anyone anymore, Say does it for them.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Citizens</strong>
              <br> it is now easy to figure out what has been said in what meeting, and when the next one will take place. Specific decisions that have been made can be found as well, just like the members of their local government can be found in a
              database.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Third parties</strong>
              <br> the data is open for anyone who would want to use and reuse it. Organising a hackathon or fueling a research paper for a student? Say makes it all possible.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
